MooseX-TrackDirty-Attributes

A set of metaclass traits and base class roles to track when attributes are
sullied.  (That is, they're set at at any point post-construction by an
accessor/writer.)

INSTALLATION

To install this module, run the following commands:

	perl Makefile.PL
	make
	make test
	make install

SUPPORT AND DOCUMENTATION

After installing, you can find documentation for this module with the
perldoc command.

    perldoc MooseX::TrackDirty::Attributes

You can also look for information at:

    RT, CPAN's request tracker
        http://rt.cpan.org/NoAuth/Bugs.html?Dist=MooseX-TrackDirty-Attributes

    AnnoCPAN, Annotated CPAN documentation
        http://annocpan.org/dist/MooseX-TrackDirty-Attributes

    CPAN Ratings
        http://cpanratings.perl.org/d/MooseX-TrackDirty-Attributes

    Search CPAN
        http://search.cpan.org/dist/MooseX-TrackDirty-Attributes/


